Reposted from @rockthebells On January 5, 1980, The Sugarhill Gang's "Rapper's Delight" became the first rap record to hit the Billboard Hot 100, reaching #37. The song, which uses an interpolation of Chic's 1979 summer anthem "Good Times," actually reached number 4 on the Hot Soul Singles chart (now known as Hit R&B/Hip Hop Songs) on December 1, 1979.

Released on September 16, 1979, "Rapper's Delight" is regarded as rap music's first commercially successful recording and the introduction of the genre to those outside of New York's 5 boroughs. It has been remade and covered by groups like Def Squad (@erick_sermon @keithmurrayrap @redmangilla) and movies like @adamsandler’s The Wedding Singer. 

Hit the link in bio to peep the full story by @jayquan_hiphop_historian

Reposted @dead_press The year is 19Naughty3' and the energetic trio from New Jersey is out with their third studio album. @tommyboyrecords has undoubtedly signed gold again and @naughtybynature4ever is climbing all the way to the top of the Billboard Hip Hop & R&B. Crazy that this record has turned 30 years old already, as with many other records now they make me realize that I'm not in my youth anymore. Very glad they chose to give this album a proper tribute by releasing this fantastic repress. The music undoubtedly helps to improve the mood and the production is rock solid. They have mostly been behind the levers themselves, which I think is very impressive. The trio from Jersey are simply tailor-made for each other and it really shines through this project. Some legendary guests have also taken the time to spread joy behind the mic. Heavy D and @queenlatifah are among them. "19Naughtylll" is a certified classic in my book and you should secure this one while you can. This is a must have for all heads out there and is something I can play no matter what mood I'm in. It will get some deserved love on my turntable today! What are your thoughts on this project?🟠

 Reposted @tommyboyrecords #TommyBoyTuesday Queen Latifah's "All Hail The Queen" album stands as a remarkable testament to the talent and commanding presence of the legendary rapper, actress, and singer. Released in 1989, this iconic work cemented Latifah's status as a trailblazer in the male-dominated hip-hop industry. The album features a seamless fusion of powerful rhymes, socially conscious lyrics, and infectious beats that captivate listeners from start to finish.

"All Hail The Queen" showcases Queen Latifah's incredible versatility as an artist. From the empowering anthem "Ladies First," which celebrates female solidarity and resilience, to the thought-provoking "Wrath of My Madness," where she fearlessly addresses societal issues and personal experiences, the album exudes confidence and authenticity. Latifah's smooth delivery, coupled with her unwavering charisma, creates an immersive experience that resonates with audiences to this day. "All Hail The Queen" is a timeless masterpiece that not only established Queen Latifah as a force to be reckoned with in hip-hop but also paved the way for future generations of female artists, inspiring them to embrace their power and voice. 

Listen to Queen Latifah’s ‘All Hail The Queen!’ 🎧: https://tommyboyrecords.lnk.to/AllHailTheQueen

Reposted @balleralert Kevin Hart’s Hartbeat Partners With BET to Bring Back ‘Comic View’ Stand-Up Comedy Showcase

Blogged by @pistolwhippedya 

If BET’s Comic View was the highlight of some of your past days, then you’ll be happy to know it is being revived.

#KevinHart and his entertainment company Hartbeat have joined forces with the Paramount Global network to bring back the stand-up comedy showcase.

“I’m thrilled to partner with BET for the return of ‘Comic View’ as part of Hartbeat Weekend making this can’t-miss celebration of comedy, music, and culture,” Hart said in a statement. “Having hosted ‘Comic View’ in the past, I understand first-hand the incredible platform this franchise offers for comedians to showcase their talents on a national stage and I’m excited to continue that tradition in Las Vegas.”

The series originally aired from 1992 to 2008, then returned with new episodes from 2012-14.

The relaunch is part of a four-day weekend event in Las Vegas celebrating Hart’s 44th birthday, Variety reported.

The comedian is hosting Hartbeat Weekend in Las Vegas from July 6-9.

Mike Epps was tapped to host the all-new episodes of “Comic View,” which will be recorded in front of a live audience during the four-day event with performances by Tommy Davidson, Tacarra Williams, Tony T. Roberts, Bresha Webb, D.C. Young Fly, and rapper Tip “T.I.” Harris.

T.I.’s show will mark his televised stand-up comedy debut.

“We’re excited to partner again with Hartbeat to bring back our culturally iconic franchise ‘Comic View’ during Hartbeat Weekend. Over 30 years ago, ‘Comic View’ set the footprint for stand-up specials and launched the careers of some of today’s mega-comedy stars. We can’t wait to see this new group of talented and rising comedians. We are so proud to work with this all-star production team, including Mike Epps and the impressive roster of talent that will bring you the best comedy you’ll see all year long,” BET president and CEO Scott Mills said.

The Great Reset!!!!! Reposted @kanekallaway Leo Messi just changed the business of sports forever.

He was reportedly offered up to $1.7B to play in Saudi Arabia.

He said no.

Instead, he signed with Inter Miami (MLS) in one of the greatest sports deals of all time.

In addition to salary, Messi is being offered:
1. A share of MLS League Pass streaming revenue (from Apple)
2. A share of all MLS apparel profits (from Adidas)
3. The right to an ownership stake in an MLS team after he’s done playing (from the MLS)

My big takeaway is that this could change the way all sports leagues operate. 

Will other stars demand ownership and uncapped upside in their respective leagues?
